  <sect2 role="installation">
    <title>Installation de XKeyboardConfig</title>

    <para>
      Installez <application>XKeyboardConfig</application> en lançant les
commandes suivantes&nbsp;:
    </para>

<screen><userinput>sed -i -E 's/(ln -s)/\1f/' rules/meson.build &amp;&amp;

mkdir build &amp;&amp;
cd    build &amp;&amp;

meson --prefix=$XORG_PREFIX --buildtype=release .. &amp;&amp;
ninja</userinput></screen>

    <para>
      Ce paquet n'a pas de suite de tests.
    </para>

    <para>
      Maintenant, en tant qu'utilisateur <systemitem
class="username">root</systemitem>&nbsp;:
    </para>

<screen role="root"><userinput>ninja install</userinput></screen>

  </sect2>
  <sect2 role="commands">
    <title>Explication des commandes</title>

    <para>
      <command>sed ... rules/meson.build</command>&nbsp;: s'assure qu'un lien
symbolique est créé même s'il existe déjà.
    </para>


  <!--
    <para>

      <parameter>- -with-xkb-rules-symlink=xorg</parameter>: By default, the
      XKB rules installed are named "base". This creates symlinks named
      "xorg" to those rules, which is the default name used by Xorg.
    </para>
-->
</sect2>
